en:
According to Article 19 of Law 8,213, "a work-related accident is one that occurs during the exercise of work at the service of the company, or during the exercise of work by a special insured person, causing bodily injury or functional disturbance, either temporary or permanent." This injury can result in death, loss, or reduction of work capacity. The injury can be characterized simply by the reduction of the function of a certain organ or body segment, such as limbs.<br>
Work-related accidents are classified into three types:

1) **Typical accident** – arising from the nature of the professional activity performed by the individual;  
2) **Commuting accident** – occurs during the commute between the worker's residence and the workplace, or vice-versa;  
3) **Occupational or work-related disease** – triggered by the performance of a specific function, characteristic of a specific job.
